article.headline: Cal Poly 67, UC Riverside 64
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Derek Stockalper hit a layup with 23 seconds remaining to seal Cal Poly's 67-64 victory over UC Riverside Saturday. Stockalper's right-handed leaner from the right block was one of three key baskets Cal Poly players hit late in the Big West Conference game. Guard Trae Clark and Titus Shelton added turnaround jumpers from the paint down the stretch to put Cal Poly ahead 65-61. Riverside guard Larry Cunningham hit a 3-pointer with 42.9 seconds left to set up Stockalper's layup. Stockalper finished with 13 points and eight rebounds. Shelton also had 13 points to go along with six rebounds. Tyler McGinn added a game-high 18 points on 7-of-12 shooting for the Mustangs (6-6, 1-1). UC Riverside (3-10, 0-2) was led by Chris Johnson's 14 points. Henrik Thomsen (13) and Justin Bell (12) also reached double figures.
